# Keep Plan Files Up to Date

After completing any task, check whether the work done affects any plan or roadmap file and update it to reflect the current state.

## Files to Maintain

- `docs/ProxDroid_Roadmap.md` – primary roadmap; tracks phases, tasks, and completion status

## What to Update

- Mark completed checklist items with `[x]` (was `[ ]`)
- Update phase status labels (e.g. `In Progress`, `Complete`) when a phase milestone is reached
- Add newly discovered tasks or sub-tasks that emerged during implementation
- Update the roadmap opening **Status:** line (see `docs/ProxDroid_Roadmap.md` line 3) when overall status changes — the roadmap is plain Markdown, not YAML frontmatter

## When to Update

- After finishing a feature, fix, or setup step that corresponds to a tracked roadmap item
- After completing a phase or milestone
- When a planned task turns out to be unnecessary — mark it as `~~skipped~~` or remove it with a note

## Example

```markdown
# Before
- [ ] Create GitHub repository (`proxdroid`)

# After completing the task
- [x] Create GitHub repository (`proxdroid`)
```

Only update the plan files that are actually affected by the work done. Do not rewrite unrelated sections.
